=E2=80=99s an important position to me right now.
<br/><br/><b>You lived through Trump I=E2=80=94that=E2=80=99s how you came =
to office, in a lot of ways. What=E2=80=99s your mindset going into Trump I=
I? </b><br/><br/>We know that Trump is extremely good at throwing out red m=
eat on five or 10 different issues in a given day. One of the mistakes Demo=
crats made back in his first term was not separating the wheat from chaff. =
I thought a lot about that from a national security [perspective]. I gamed =
out a kind of decision tree on which issues I really must engage in, and wh=
ich issues are more fleeting. <br/><br/>When Trump does something on a give=
n day that I don=E2=80=99t agree with, I think, is it tactical? Is it strat=
egic? And then: Is it reversible or irreversible? And something that=E2=80=
=99s irreversible and strategic should get my attention, and something that=
